claim.claim-text:
1. A method for focusing proteins comprising:
providing a plurality of nanofluidic channels, wherein one of a width and a depth of each nanofluidic channel is about 1000 nm or less;
equilibrating a buffer solution with walls of the plurality of nanofluidic channels suitable for the proteins to be focused by determining an equilibrium time by IR absorbance spectra;
introducing a protein mixture solution that contains a plurality of proteins into the nanofluidic channels; and
applying an electric potential to a length of the protein mixture solution along the nanofluidic channels to generate a longitudinal electric field.
